  • Type Parameters:
    Q - The quantity of the values that are stored here.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<Constraint<Q>>, java.util.Collection<Constraint<Q>>, java.util.List<Constraint<Q>>

    public class ConstraintList<Q extends javax.measure.quantity.Quantity>
extends java.util.AbstractList<Constraint<Q>>
    The ConstraintList is used as a method to describe several modes. It is most commonly used for representing different possible charge speeds in a buffer. This is a list of several values or ranges of values.
